<p>I have data like this:</p>  <pre><code>[   {id: 1, x:10, y:20, a: 123},   {id: 2, x:20, y:12}, ] </code></pre>  <p>I want generate DOM to look something like this:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;div style='top:20px; left: 10px'&gt;   &lt;strong&gt;1&lt;/strong&gt;   &lt;span&gt;123&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div style='top:12px; left: 20px'&gt;   &lt;strong&gt;2&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/div&gt; </code></pre>  <p><strong>Is there a way to append elements based on the existence of attributes?</strong></p>  <p>Also a way to remove them if a new version of the data is missing those attributes?</p>